OL,3,CSalford-based BBC News at One launches
OL,4,Ctomorrow
OL,6,GMonday's relaunch of the BBC News at
OL,7,GOne is high stakes. If it goes wrong
OL,8,Gfor any reason, there could be serious
OL,9,Grepercussions.
OL,11,FThe programme is both an important
OL,12,Fpublic service responsibility and the
OL,13,FBBC's most-watched daytime programme.
OL,15,FIt routinely attracts 2m viewers and
OL,16,Foften gains more, especially if there
OL,17,Fis a big story or If bad weather keeps
OL,18,Fpeople off work.
OL,20,FThe revamp means a number of changes:
