OL,4,Ctomorrow
OL,6,FThere are two audiences for the BBC
OL,7,FNews at One: people who switch on to
OL,8,Fwatch the lunchtime news, perhaps on
OL,9,Ftheir break, and people at home all
OL,10,Fday who may watch other afternoon
OL,11,Fprogrammes.
OL,13,FThe regional opt will happen at
OL,14,Fapproximately the established time of
OL,15,F1.35pm.
OL,17,FThis suggests the plan is to keep the
OL,18,Fformat and content of the first half
OL,19,Fof the programme pretty much as before.
OL,21,FIt would be a mistake not to.
OL,1,W~+$ hw1~{4~k4 ~shw1~sj7}         G4/8
